The Surname and Query File is a service provided to researchers and visitors.  It is a file of the surnames that researchers are searching or may be seeking information about. This file has been quite useful in helping researchers connect with other researchers with a common interest in a specific surname.  Many cousins have discovered each other through this service.

 

If you wish to post a surname or request information regarding a specific person, please send you request to the webmaster at:  richardharrington@cox.net.

ADAMS

Suzanne Adams 1633 SW Gemini Lane,

Port St. Lucie, FL  34984

TeacherG4@aol.com

I am a descendent of James Adams born on or about 1833in VA and moved to Monroe County, OHIO before 1855.  Both his parents are from Ireland.  His parents names are James Adams and Sarah Adams.  The aforementioned James married Anna or Hanna Sykes or Six of PA or OH.  Their children according to the 1860 and 1870 censuses are:  Sarah L, David N, Marshal V, Ruth A, Cora J, James, Ellwood or Ellsworth, William, and Ode J.

Sarah L became Sarah McDonald, and Ruth A Became Ruth Stevens.

This family moved to Sedalia, MO shortly after the civil war and are found in the 1870 census in FLat Creek.  In the 1880 census the parents cannot be found and all the children are either on their own, married, and the minor children are living with relatives.  My guess is that a tragedy befell this family and both mother and father were killed and all the children were forced to fare on their own and rely on other family until they were old enough to become independent.  If something did happen to the family, it should be recorded somewhere.  Maybe in old newspapers or records in your library.

In the 1880 census Ode Jane Adams resides with  an aunt Lutitia Morrow and William Adams resides with his grandmother.  David, Marshall (M.V.) and Ellsworth (E.M.) are all loggers in Montana in 1880.  It is obvious that the family met with some tragedy where both parents died of disease, or were injured and possibly were killed. 

Any assistance figuring out what happened to this family and why the children were separated and living with relatives would be greatly appreciated.
